[
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry for lack of a standalone example, I suspect it may take me a while to properly isolate it. But I'm working through <a href=\"https://github.com/ImperialCollegeLondon/formalising-mathematics-2024/blob/0eb9abdd52bde8f2ebb6fc1d4568d7f8f559c32a/FormalisingMathematics2024/Section02reals/Sheet6.lean#L55-L57\">this sheet</a> now and realize I don't understand something about <code>rw</code>.</p>\n<p>This is what I have at the beginning:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_mul_const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a : ℕ → ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  t c : ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  h : TendsTo a t</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ TendsTo (fun n ↦ a n * c) (t * c)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What I'd like to is to turn <code>a n * c</code> into <code>c * a n</code> in the goal. This should help me because I have a proof of a relevant theorem earlier in the file.</p>\n<p>Initially I just tried to do this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_mul_const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">mul_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- swaps `t` and `c`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But this swaps <code>c * t</code> to <code>t * c</code> and doesn't seem to even \"notice\" <code>fun n ↦ a n * c</code> inside the goal.</p>\n<p>I have a few questions:</p>\n<p>What should my mental model of this be? Is <code>rw</code> averse to stepping into functions, but something else may help? Is it \"impossible\" to step into functions in general without actually unwinding the goal, even if the statement we're replacing is clearly equivalent? Is it <em>not</em> \"clearly equivalent\" at this point because we're operating at a semantic rather than syntactic level and thus we have to actually \"get deeper\"?</p>\n<p>It seems that this isn't specific to functions anyway. This doesn't help either:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_mul_const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_def</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">mul_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- swaps `t` and `c`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The earliest I can make <code>rw</code> do the thing that I want is right after defining <code>n</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_mul_const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">TendsTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">tendsTo_def</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ε</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hε</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">mul_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- swaps `a n` and `c`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So is the problem here that <code>n</code> is a free variable, and <code>rw</code> can't work with free variables? Is there something else that can? Is my request unreasonable, i.e. is replacement with free variables fundamentally unsound? If yes, what's a counterexample showing why it is unsound?</p>",
